title:
A hack to support array types in Squid's Config structure.  Mostly this
is to eliminate compiler warnings.  The compiler wants us to write
   parse_bar(&Config.bar[0]);
rather than
   parse_bar(&Config.bar);

DW:
 - Changed occurances of

        struct _foo {
            /* first two items must be same as hash_link */
            char *key;
            foo *next;
            ...
        };

   to

        struct _foo {
            hash_link hash;     /* must be first */
            ...
        };

- changed internal structure of HttpBody to use MemBuf;
  no more inconsistencies with body.size
- removed HTML tags from mgr:http_headers dump
